  "body": "### Component\n\nFoundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nmaster branch\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nfoundryup\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/6352 has made `foundryup` stricter.\r\nThis has created a breaking change in how `foundryup` behaves: if `FOUNDRY_BIN_DIR` is not in the `PATH`, `foundryup` will fail because the `which` command will fail, and the script will stop.\r\nThis means the binaries will be installed, but the script will exit with a status of 1.\r\n",
